						<summary>

						<p>MADRAS.</p>						

						<p>Slabs in the underground room in the Government Museum, Madras</p>						

						<p>••• ••• ••• •••••</p>						

						<p>Written in the Sanskrit language and in Southern characters of about the 6th century A.D., This inscription seems to record the obeisance to the <hi rend="italic">chatiya</hi> with the big idol, of Paṁchavāri-chaṁdra-kuśalakāri on his visit. </p>						

						</summary>
